1
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:15,033
<i> Sweetie, you called.</i>

2
00:00:15,167 --> 00:00:16,200
<i>You know, I've been trying
to locate you in Australia</i>

3
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:17,333
<i> for so long.</i>

4
00:00:17,467 --> 00:00:18,667
<i>Because I really
wanted to come see you.</i>

5
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,467
<i> Please come here.</i>

6
00:00:20,600 --> 00:00:22,200
<i> I'll send you our address.</i>

7
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:24,100
<i>Sweetie, your mom
might get mad.</i>

8
00:00:24,233 --> 00:00:25,167
<i> I also want you to come.</i>

9
00:00:25,300 --> 00:00:27,733
<i>So I can apologize
to you in person.</i>

10
00:00:27,867 --> 00:00:30,733
<i>Coleen, Andrea, please
take care of Mom and Dad</i>

11
00:00:30,867 --> 00:00:31,667
<i> for now, okay?</i>

12
00:00:31,800 --> 00:00:33,000
<i>I feel like going
home right away.</i>

13
00:00:34,533 --> 00:00:35,633
<i>All right, I'll miss you.
I'll be back soon.</i>

14
00:00:35,767 --> 00:00:37,033
<i> Mom?</i>

15
00:00:37,167 --> 00:00:38,300
<i> Dad?</i>

16
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:39,967
<i>I think someone's following me.</i>

17
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:40,967
<i> Help!</i>

18
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:42,200
<i> Help!</i>

19
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:44,633
<i> Help!</i>

20
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:48,700
<i> Help!</i>

21
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,333
<i> Joel, stop it.</i>

22
00:00:57,467 --> 00:00:59,467
<i> First, it was Coleen.</i>

23
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:01,467
<i> Now it's you.</i>

24
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,833
<i> Report this to the police.</i>

25
00:01:03,967 --> 00:01:05,833
<i> We already filed a report.</i>

26
00:01:05,967 --> 00:01:07,467
<i> Where are you now?</i>

27
00:01:07,633 --> 00:01:09,267
<i> We're at the hospital, Dad.</i>

28
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,667
<i> We're buying Mom's medicine.</i>

29
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:12,267
<i>Isn't it the only place
you can get it?</i>

30
00:01:16,633 --> 00:01:18,733
<i> Andrea, go ahead to the car.</i>

31
00:01:18,867 --> 00:01:19,867
<i>I just need to use the restroom.</i>

32
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:20,633
<i> Okay.</i>

33
00:01:20,767 --> 00:01:23,833
<i> Just wait for my orders.</i>

34
00:01:56,400 --> 00:01:57,100
Hey!

35
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:58,067
Hey!

36
00:02:21,533 --> 00:02:22,800
What are we going to do now?

37
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:44,300
Why did he send this to me?

38
00:02:48,433 --> 00:02:50,067
Where are you?

39
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:14,667
Jojo?

40
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:15,800
Hazel?

41
00:03:15,933 --> 00:03:16,667
What?

42
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:18,567
Are you two working together?

43
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:20,633
What are you planning to do
to Aunt Felma and her family?

44
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,633
That's none of your business.

45
00:03:22,767 --> 00:03:24,900
I'm really sick of you.

46
00:03:25,033 --> 00:03:27,033
You wanted to involve yourself
with Felma's family.

47
00:03:27,167 --> 00:03:28,267
You're not even related to them.

48
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,400
You're an outsider!

49
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:32,033
No.

50
00:03:32,167 --> 00:03:33,833
I won't let you hurt them!

51
00:03:58,467 --> 00:03:59,300
Leave.

52
00:03:59,433 --> 00:04:00,200
Just go.

53
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:02,000
What are you going
to do with him?

54
00:04:02,133 --> 00:04:03,667
I'll handle this.

55
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:04,767
Go on.

56
00:04:04,900 --> 00:04:06,900
Make sure no one sees you.

57
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:09,033
Don't pass by the
area outside, okay?

58
00:04:09,167 --> 00:04:10,133
Go!

59
00:04:25,533 --> 00:04:26,233
There you are.

60
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:27,100
So? What now?

61
00:04:27,233 --> 00:04:27,900
Is that it?

62
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:30,333
You got it?

63
00:04:30,467 --> 00:04:31,567
What do you even need that for?

64
00:04:37,067 --> 00:04:38,733
You don't have to know.

65
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,267
Don't ask anymore.

66
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:43,167
You know those meds
are dangerous.

67
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:46,467
I said don't worry about it.

68
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,200
I just have to do something.

69
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:49,900
Go back to your duty.

70
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:17,433
Ma'am?

71
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:18,467
Sir?

72
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,333
Ma'am? Sir?

73
00:05:36,900 --> 00:05:38,167
Help!

74
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:41,467
Help!

75
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,667
He's not answering.

76
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,367
Excuse me, Sir.

77
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:11,467
Where's the restroom?

78
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:12,467
Ma'am, over there.

79
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,533
Okay, thank you.

80
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:23,167
Joel?

81
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:25,267
Joel?

82
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:27,000
Doctor, what happened?

83
00:06:27,133 --> 00:06:28,533
Joel?

84
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:29,667
Joel?

85
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,567
Doctor, why?

86
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,233
Doctor, why?

87
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:34,367
Joel...

88
00:06:35,933 --> 00:06:36,633
Joel?

89
00:06:36,767 --> 00:06:37,433
Doctor, why?

90
00:06:37,567 --> 00:06:38,633
What happened?

91
00:06:38,767 --> 00:06:39,967
- Joel?
- Andrea!

92
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:40,700
Andrea!

93
00:06:40,867 --> 00:06:42,067
Alice.

94
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:43,200
- Alice, please...
- What happened?

95
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:44,133
Please help Joel.

96
00:06:44,267 --> 00:06:45,167
I'm begging you.

97
00:06:45,300 --> 00:06:46,233
Save him, please.

98
00:06:46,367 --> 00:06:47,400
Alice, please...

99
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,667
Doctor, what's going on?

100
00:07:06,167 --> 00:07:08,900
<i>You know those
drugs are dangerous.</i>

101
00:07:09,033 --> 00:07:11,700
<i> Just don't ask anymore.</i>

102
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:14,200
Check his vital signs.

103
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,633
No pulse.

104
00:07:27,300 --> 00:07:28,800
Joel...

105
00:07:33,867 --> 00:07:35,100
No BP, Doc.

106
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:36,433
Start CPR.

107
00:07:45,933 --> 00:07:47,233
Joel...

108
00:07:53,033 --> 00:07:54,433
Give him one amp of epi!

109
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:11,900
Sir, just 20 minutes
of exercise, okay?

110
00:08:12,033 --> 00:08:12,600
All right.

111
00:08:12,733 --> 00:08:13,433
Okay.

112
00:08:15,167 --> 00:08:16,167
I don't know.

113
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:18,167
The janitor found him
in the restroom.

114
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:19,267
Probably a junkie.

115
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,600
Looks like an overdose.

116
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:22,700
Excuse me, Sir.

117
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:27,167
Trisha, can you take over
my patient for now?

118
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,567
There's an emergency.

119
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:29,867
Sure, Jojo. I've got it.

120
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:30,967
Thanks.

121
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:32,167
Okay, later.

122
00:08:32,300 --> 00:08:33,200
One amp.

123
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:46,133
Give him one amp of epi!

124
00:09:04,700 --> 00:09:06,333
Why did you stop?

125
00:09:06,467 --> 00:09:08,667
Ma'am, it's no use.

126
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:09,633
I'm sorry.

127
00:09:11,900 --> 00:09:14,267
Time of death: 5:03.

128
00:09:16,833 --> 00:09:17,367
Andrea...

129
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:19,667
No!

130
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:20,833
Joel!

131
00:09:20,967 --> 00:09:22,033
Joel!

132
00:09:22,167 --> 00:09:24,767
Joel!

133
00:09:24,900 --> 00:09:26,933
Please wake up, Joel!

134
00:09:28,667 --> 00:09:30,533
Joel!

135
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:37,567
Joel...

136
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,100
Joel, I love you.

137
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:45,400
I love you so much.

138
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:51,733
I don't know when or how
it started, but I love you.

139
00:09:55,133 --> 00:09:57,633
Please, don't leave me.

140
00:09:57,767 --> 00:09:59,967
Wake up, Joel. Please.

141
00:10:02,167 --> 00:10:03,533
Please...

142
00:10:06,567 --> 00:10:08,033
Alice!

143
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:10,633
Joel!

144
00:10:10,767 --> 00:10:12,400
Joel!

145
00:10:12,533 --> 00:10:14,067
Joel, please!

146
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:35,033
<i>I swore an oath to save lives,
even the lives of people I hate.</i>

147
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:36,267
<i> I won't let you hurt them!</i>

148
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,567
<i>What do you even need that for?</i>

149
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:41,633
<i> Don't ask anymore.</i>

150
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:47,467
Hazel!

151
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,333
Hazel.

152
00:10:49,467 --> 00:10:50,700
Did you do that to Joel?

153
00:10:52,667 --> 00:10:55,300
People inside the hospital
are saying he overdosed.

154
00:10:57,533 --> 00:10:58,267
Did you kill him?

155
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:03,767
Do you think I wanted
this to happen?

156
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:06,333
All I wanted was...

157
00:11:06,467 --> 00:11:08,500
to make it look like
he was using drugs.

158
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:10,567
So if he told Felma,

159
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:13,467
they'd think
he was hallucinating.

160
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:17,767
I didn't know his body
was that weak.

161
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:21,533
And besides, Jojo,
we couldn't let him go.

162
00:11:21,667 --> 00:11:25,267
If he told Felma,
she'd report us to the police.

163
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,333
We'd both end up in jail.

164
00:11:26,467 --> 00:11:27,500
Do you want that?

165
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:30,733
You killing him was
never part of the plan.

166
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:33,700
Me?

167
00:11:34,433 --> 00:11:36,433
Just me?

168
00:11:36,567 --> 00:11:38,200
Both of us.

169
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,967
You're already in this.

170
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:42,533
We're just getting
revenge for Jessica.

171
00:11:42,700 --> 00:11:44,233
Why did it have to come to this?

172
00:11:45,367 --> 00:11:47,333
What? Are you getting scared
now?

173
00:11:47,467 --> 00:11:48,667
Are you backing out?

174
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:50,267
It's too late.

175
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:51,733
We already started this.

176
00:11:51,867 --> 00:11:53,000
There's no turning back.

177
00:11:54,300 --> 00:11:55,533
Just think about this.

178
00:11:55,667 --> 00:11:58,067
If it weren't for Felma's
family's abuse,

179
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,433
our child would still be alive.

180
00:12:00,567 --> 00:12:01,967
We'd still be together.

181
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:06,200
You want to make it up to
Jessica, right?

182
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:08,767
This is your chance.

183
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:10,967
Get revenge.

184
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:13,067
And one more thing.
Get yourself together.

185
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,700
Because we're not done yet.

186
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:24,233
Ma'am, how are you
related to Joel Santiago?

187
00:12:24,967 --> 00:12:26,433
He's my friend.

188
00:12:26,567 --> 00:12:29,100
We need to speak
with his family,

189
00:12:29,233 --> 00:12:34,567
so we can include his personal
belongings in the investigation.

190
00:12:34,700 --> 00:12:37,133
I already called his sibling.

191
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:40,267
What exactly happened to Joel?

192
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:42,500
Based on our initial
investigation,

193
00:12:42,633 --> 00:12:46,200
we found a puncture mark
on his left arm.

194
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:49,633
It suggests a drug
was injected there.

195
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:53,067
We also found a syringe
in his right hand

196
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:55,367
and a small vial of medicine.

197
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:59,733
We're verifying with toxicology
what kind of drug it was.

198
00:12:59,867 --> 00:13:02,533
This could be a
drug overdose case.

199
00:13:02,667 --> 00:13:03,967
But...

200
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:08,800
But Joel isn't a user.

201
00:13:08,933 --> 00:13:10,100
I've known him for a long time.

202
00:13:10,233 --> 00:13:12,700
No, he doesn't do drugs.

203
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:16,667
We still need to speak
with his family.

204
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:20,867
You can talk to his siblings,
his mother, or anyone.

205
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,933
All of us know Joel
wasn't an addict.

206
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:27,733
Maybe he was dealing
with something,

207
00:13:27,867 --> 00:13:30,433
something he couldn't tell you.

208
00:13:30,567 --> 00:13:32,667
Are you saying Joel
harmed himself?

209
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:36,700
No.

210
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:37,867
He would never do that.

211
00:13:39,067 --> 00:13:42,000
In fact, he was fine.

212
00:13:42,133 --> 00:13:43,800
We were fine.

213
00:13:43,933 --> 00:13:46,167
He was happy with our
friendship, with my family.

214
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,667
With the family he had.

215
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:50,933
He had so many plans.

216
00:14:04,033 --> 00:14:04,967
Andeng...

217
00:14:07,100 --> 00:14:07,900
Dad...

218
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:09,867
Dad.

219
00:14:13,733 --> 00:14:14,500
Dad...

220
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,000
Dad...

221
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:26,633
Dad...

222
00:14:26,767 --> 00:14:28,833
Joel's gone.

223
00:14:30,767 --> 00:14:34,000
My best friend is gone, Dad.

224
00:14:36,367 --> 00:14:41,133
Sweetie, I saw how
he took care of you.

225
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:42,900
That's why this hurts me, too.

226
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:49,167
Andeng, in your text,

227
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:52,367
you said the police think
it was an overdose.

228
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:56,100
I don't believe
Joel would do that.

229
00:14:56,233 --> 00:14:59,233
That's what I told them, too,
Dad.

230
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:02,567
But...

231
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:05,100
but...

232
00:15:05,233 --> 00:15:08,000
Who would do this to Joel?

233
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:11,400
Why would they kill him?

234
00:15:15,033 --> 00:15:17,433
Why? Why, Dad?

235
00:15:42,767 --> 00:15:43,600
<i> Jessica!</i>

236
00:15:43,733 --> 00:15:44,400
<i> What did you do?</i>

237
00:15:44,533 --> 00:15:46,100
<i> I didn't do anything!</i>

238
00:15:46,233 --> 00:15:48,433
<i> I didn't do anything!</i>

239
00:15:48,567 --> 00:15:50,167
<i> Jessica!</i>

240
00:15:50,300 --> 00:15:51,400
<i> Okay, fine.</i>

241
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:51,967
<i> You're angry.</i>

242
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:53,067
<i> You want revenge.</i>

243
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:55,300
<i> But to destroy her reputation?</i>

244
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:56,400
<i> To break her spirit?</i>

245
00:15:56,533 --> 00:15:58,033
<i> To tear my family apart?</i>

246
00:15:58,167 --> 00:16:00,033
<i> I'll help Coleen.</i>

247
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:01,400
<i>Let's get back together, Manuel.</i>

248
00:16:01,533 --> 00:16:05,567
<i>Let's rebuild our family
and fulfill Jessica's last wish.</i>

249
00:16:05,700 --> 00:16:07,200
<i>I will never get back
together with you!</i>

250
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:10,900
<i> Yes, Hazel, you're my wife.</i>

251
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:11,933
<i> On paper.</i>

252
00:16:12,067 --> 00:16:14,200
<i>But Felma, she is the one
I truly love.</i>

253
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:15,400
<i> I came back to you</i>

254
00:16:15,533 --> 00:16:18,300
<i>because you said you'd help
clear Coleen's name.</i>

255
00:16:18,433 --> 00:16:20,733
<i> That doesn't mean I love you.</i>

256
00:16:20,867 --> 00:16:23,400
<i>He'll love me once
we're together again...</i>

257
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:26,500
<i> Once I show him my love.</i>

258
00:16:26,633 --> 00:16:28,267
<i> How I take care of him.</i>

259
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:29,933
<i> I'll devote myself to him</i>

260
00:16:30,067 --> 00:16:34,367
<i>until he finally sees
that I'm worth loving.</i>

261
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:36,000
<i> Don't get your hopes up.</i>

262
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:37,867
<i> He loves me.</i>

263
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:40,533
<i> Only me.</i>

264
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,833
Rejection after rejection.

265
00:16:48,667 --> 00:16:50,833
You've wronged me
over and over, Felma.

266
00:16:56,333 --> 00:16:58,667
I'm not just getting revenge
for Jessica, Manuel.

267
00:16:59,667 --> 00:17:00,933
I'm also getting revenge
for myself.

268
00:17:03,300 --> 00:17:05,233
I'm sorry, Joel.

269
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:07,200
I didn't mean for this
to happen to you.

270
00:17:08,900 --> 00:17:10,667
But all of you better
be ready...

271
00:17:13,167 --> 00:17:14,700
because I'm not stopping.

272
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:22,767
I'm not stopping.

273
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,467
It all happened so fast.

274
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:40,733
I was just texting Joel earlier.

275
00:17:41,833 --> 00:17:44,367
And now he's gone.

276
00:17:44,500 --> 00:17:45,800
So he was a drug addict?

277
00:17:45,933 --> 00:17:47,533
Didn't really fit him.

278
00:17:48,633 --> 00:17:51,400
He really wasn't a user.

279
00:17:52,433 --> 00:17:54,267
He was a good person.

280
00:17:56,300 --> 00:18:00,133
He knew what was right for him.

281
00:18:00,267 --> 00:18:02,733
Maybe he was depressed.

282
00:18:02,867 --> 00:18:04,267
You know?

283
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:06,333
Didang, it just feels
impossible.

284
00:18:06,467 --> 00:18:09,267
He was always making
Andrea happy.

285
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:12,800
What's impossible about that?
Some people are like that.

286
00:18:12,933 --> 00:18:18,200
You think they're happy.
Always smiling. Always joking.

287
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:22,100
But deep inside, when they're
alone, they're depressed.

288
00:18:22,267 --> 00:18:24,133
They've already given up
on life.

289
00:18:25,233 --> 00:18:27,767
Joel wasn't like that.

290
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:31,900
He never gave up on Andrea.

291
00:18:32,033 --> 00:18:35,100
He was trying to win her up
to the last moment.

292
00:18:36,233 --> 00:18:38,133
So what really happened?

293
00:18:39,167 --> 00:18:41,033
You know what, Ma'am?

294
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:45,767
Maybe we should call Jeff and
ask him. They're close, right?

295
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:47,500
Maybe he knows something.

296
00:18:47,633 --> 00:18:48,967
No.

297
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:51,900
This isn't the right time.

298
00:18:52,033 --> 00:18:53,500
Especially now.

299
00:18:53,633 --> 00:18:56,133
He's finally with his family.

300
00:19:00,133 --> 00:19:01,167
Hazel!

301
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:02,333
Hazel!

302
00:19:02,467 --> 00:19:04,500
Perfect timing. Come here.

303
00:19:04,633 --> 00:19:05,767
Hazel!

304
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:07,467
Do you even understand
what you did?

305
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:09,200
Hazel, you killed someone.

306
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:11,133
That's not what we do.

307
00:19:11,267 --> 00:19:13,033
We're nurses.

308
00:19:13,167 --> 00:19:15,467
We save lives.

309
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:18,500
I know.

310
00:19:19,967 --> 00:19:22,300
So why do you seem so calm?

311
00:19:22,433 --> 00:19:23,867
Are you even thinking straight?

312
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:27,733
I am thinking straight.

313
00:19:27,900 --> 00:19:29,833
That's why I acted fast.

314
00:19:30,967 --> 00:19:32,700
What happened to Joel...

315
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:34,633
wasn't intentional.

316
00:19:34,767 --> 00:19:37,733
Is it my fault his body
was weak?

317
00:19:37,867 --> 00:19:38,800
Fine.

318
00:19:38,933 --> 00:19:41,100
Let's say I did mean it.

319
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:43,267
He deserved it.

320
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:46,600
Because everything Jojo and I
worked for would've been ruined.

321
00:19:46,733 --> 00:19:47,600
Sit down.

322
00:19:47,733 --> 00:19:48,633
Let's eat.

323
00:19:51,233 --> 00:19:52,867
My God.

324
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,900
Your anger has completely
consumed you.

325
00:19:56,033 --> 00:19:58,333
Maybe getting justice
for Jessica was right,

326
00:19:58,467 --> 00:20:00,533
but killing someone?

327
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:02,467
Hazel, I don't even recognize
you anymore.

328
00:20:03,867 --> 00:20:04,867
So...

329
00:20:05,967 --> 00:20:07,533
you don't want to be
my friend anymore?

330
00:20:08,967 --> 00:20:10,567
Let me remind you.

331
00:20:11,633 --> 00:20:13,800
That drug I injected
into Joel...

332
00:20:13,933 --> 00:20:15,500
came from you.

333
00:20:15,633 --> 00:20:18,167
So what does that make you?

334
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,033
An accessory to the crime?

335
00:20:21,133 --> 00:20:23,633
If I knew you'd use it like
this,

336
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:25,333
I never would've given
it to you.

337
00:20:25,467 --> 00:20:27,467
But you still gave it to me.

338
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:30,667
So you're just as guilty
as I am.

339
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,700
Hazel, do you even have
a conscience?

340
00:20:35,633 --> 00:20:37,100
Can you really blame me?

341
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:42,167
After everything Felma
and Manuel did to me?

342
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:45,567
So, if I were you...

343
00:20:46,967 --> 00:20:49,233
instead of guilt-tripping me,

344
00:20:49,367 --> 00:20:51,500
just leave me alone.

345
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:55,133
Let me do what I want to
that illegitimate family.

346
00:20:59,267 --> 00:21:00,833
Please pass the rice.

347
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,533
Thank you.

348
00:21:12,167 --> 00:21:15,000
Thank you, Andrea,
for everything you did for Joel.

349
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:18,967
And to your family, too.

350
00:21:20,067 --> 00:21:23,933
Thank you so much for welcoming
our brother

351
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:25,533
as part of your family.

352
00:21:25,967 --> 00:21:28,600
Thank you for...

353
00:21:28,733 --> 00:21:30,533
sharing him with us.

354
00:21:32,433 --> 00:21:35,233
It's really sad, Andrea.

355
00:21:35,367 --> 00:21:37,667
Joel used to talk about you all
the time.

356
00:21:38,667 --> 00:21:41,033
You were the only one he ever
took seriously.

357
00:21:41,167 --> 00:21:42,833
If you'd said yes back then

358
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,767
maybe it would've led
to marriage.

359
00:21:44,900 --> 00:21:46,867
You could've been
our sister-in-law.

360
00:22:08,867 --> 00:22:11,033
You know, Andrea...

361
00:22:11,167 --> 00:22:14,267
Even if you didn't say yes
to Joel,

362
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:17,200
it still felt like we gained
a brother-in-law.

363
00:22:17,367 --> 00:22:18,367
And a son-in-law.

364
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:24,200
To be honest,
I treated him like...

365
00:22:24,333 --> 00:22:25,533
like my own son.

366
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:28,867
Even if we'd ended up
together...

367
00:22:30,700 --> 00:22:33,033
if this is how things were going
to turn out for him,

368
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:36,867
maybe it would've been better
if we'd never met at all.

369
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:41,600
How's the investigation going?

370
00:22:41,733 --> 00:22:44,233
I talked to the police.

371
00:22:44,367 --> 00:22:48,400
They said they're looking into
the possibility of foul play.

372
00:22:48,567 --> 00:22:50,400
That someone else did this
to Joel.

373
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:55,400
But when they checked the CCTV
in the area

374
00:22:55,533 --> 00:22:57,733
to identify who did it they
found nothing.

375
00:22:57,867 --> 00:22:59,533
<i> The cameras were broken.</i>

376
00:22:59,667 --> 00:23:02,167
You know what? I could also
ask for...

377
00:23:02,300 --> 00:23:04,333
help from Colonel Sarabia.

378
00:23:04,467 --> 00:23:07,933
It's reassuring that the
hospital administration

379
00:23:08,067 --> 00:23:11,067
is cooperating
with the investigation.

380
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:14,367
Whoever did this to Joel...

381
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:16,367
whoever killed him...

382
00:23:17,567 --> 00:23:19,500
I hope they're caught soon.

383
00:23:19,633 --> 00:23:23,267
And I hope they rot in prison
for life.
